        <definition>typedef void(* ClickConfigProvider) (void *context)</definition>
        <argsstring>)(void *context)</argsstring>
        <name>ClickConfigProvider</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This callback is called every time the window becomes visible (and when you call <ref refid="group___window_1gaeefbe33bc69ffee444337b056912440c" kindref="member">window_set_click_config_provider()</ref> if the window is already visible). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Subscribe to click events using <ref refid="group___window_1gae09d8d7299a9d5a750a898a70f64bdec" kindref="member">window_single_click_subscribe()</ref> <ref refid="group___window_1ga1ff2467f009b80f8bc97ef197e34d332" kindref="member">window_single_repeating_click_subscribe()</ref> <ref refid="group___window_1ga041018e3b3db5bb7866283fffcd4b766" kindref="member">window_multi_click_subscribe()</ref> <ref refid="group___window_1ga3329027de707b949f02328492165cf05" kindref="member">window_long_click_subscribe()</ref> <ref refid="group___window_1ga6cecc4f27755aaf91f1f232c4c6f8b16" kindref="member">window_raw_click_subscribe()</ref> These subscriptions will get used by the click recognizers of each of the 4 buttons. <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>context</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to application specific data (see <ref refid="group___window_1gadfbe85cbdb8a0b96d970672639c5421e" kindref="member">window_set_click_config_provider_with_context()</ref>). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
